15 October</link> <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../598/34598.xml">
1993</link>)  Graduated with honors from the <link>
Moscow Institute of Chemical Machine-Building</link> in 1934 and worked as an engineer in a chemical plant for several years in the <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../930/480930.xml">
Tula</link> region. Continued  postgraduate engineering studies and joined the <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../958/16958.xml">
KGB</link> in 1938 as a specialist in scientific-technical intelligence.  Beginning in 1939 he was the section head of scientific and technical intelligence. Kvasnikov served a few short-term assignments in <country wordnetid="108544813" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../867/11867.xml">
